<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm">
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Fill_area +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area"><p>

 A <b>Fill_area</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Associative_text:arm:Associative_text_arm.Annotation_element"/>. A <b>Fill_area</b> is the area bounded by a <express_ref linkend="Associative_text:arm:Associative_text_arm.Annotation_curve"/> that is defined to be filled 
with material using a pattern.  Each  <express_ref linkend="Associative_text:arm:Associative_text_arm.Annotation_curve"/> shall be an outer or inner boundary.  Each boundary shall be closed.  
There shall be no more than one outer boundary.  No boundary shall self-intersect or intersect with any other boundary.
</p><note>
This Application Object is describing geometric patterns.  The association of material with the patterns
occurs elsewhere, for instance in the  <express_ref linkend="Interconnect_2d_shape:arm:Interconnect_2d_shape_arm.Design_intent_modification_styled_area_representation"/>.
</note>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style.boundary">
specifies the <express_ref linkend="Associative_text:arm:Associative_text_arm.Annotation_curve"/> that describes the outline of the 
<b>Fill_area</b>. There shall be one or more  <express_ref linkend="Associative_text:arm:Associative_text_arm.Annotation_curve"/> for a <b>Fill_area</b>.
The curves shall be non-self intersecting and non-overlapping.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style.reference_point">
specifies one of <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/>, <express_ref linkend="Basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Point_on_curve"/> or <express_ref linkend="Basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Point_on_surface"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- +++++++++++ Fill_area_occurrence +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_occurrence">

 A <b>Fill_area_occurrence</b> is an instantiation of a <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area"/>.  The <b>boundary_style</b> shall be applied to each boundary of the instance fo the  <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area"/>.  A zero width <b>boundary_style</b> shall be interpreted as using the boundaries of the  <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area"/> as clipping regions.  A non-zero width <b>boundary_style</b> shall be interpreted as the regularlized Boolean "OR" operation on the instance of the  <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area"/>, applied at each boundary after the clip operation required by the zero width boundary <b>style</b>.  The orientation of the  <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area"/> instances shall be parallel with the orientation of the  <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_occurrence.boundary_style">
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Styled_curve:arm:Styled_curve_arm.Curve_style"/> for the 
<b>Fill_area_occurrence</b>.  The <b>boundary_style</b> is applied to each instance of the  <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area"/> boundaries individually.  The <b>boundary_style</b> end parameters shall be ignored.  The <b>boundary_style</b> <express_ref linkend="Styled_curve:arm:Styled_curve_arm.Curve_style.curve_font"/> shall not be specified.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_occurrence.fill_style_target">
specifies the <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/> that 
defines the location of the <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style"/> for the 
<b>Fill_area_occurrence</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_occurrence.filled_area">
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area"/> for the <b>Fill_area_occurrence</b>.  The  <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area"/> provides shape and orientation information for the <b>Fill_area_occurrence</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_occurrence.style">
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style"/> for the 
<b>Fill_area_occurrence</b>. There shall be one or more  <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style"/> for a <b>Fill_area_occurrence</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Fill_area_style +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style">

 A <b>Fill_area_style</b> is the selected style used in 
a <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style.fill_style">
specifies the <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.fill_style_select"/> for the <b>Fill_area_style</b>.
The <b>fill_style</b> specifies either an <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Externally_defined_hatch_style"/>, 
an <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Externally_defined_tile_style"/>, a <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style_hatching"/>, 
a <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style_tile"/>, or a <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Solid_fill_style"/>
for the <b>Fill_area_style</b>. 
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style.name">
the words by which the <b>Fill_area_style</b> is known.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style.ur:UR1">
The <b>name</b> shall be unique within a population of <b>Fill_area_style</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Fill_area_style_hatching +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style_hatching"><p>

 A <b>Fill_area_style_hatching</b> is the parallel line hatch style of a <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area"/>.  All units associated with <b>Fill_area_style_hatching</b> are defined in the global units for the <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Interconnect_module"/> being designed.  The geometric reference for <b>Fill_area_style_hatching</b> shall be the origin of the  <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Interconnect_module"/> being designed.  When this Application Object is used to help compose a <express_ref linkend="Interconnect_2d_shape:arm:Interconnect_2d_shape_arm.Design_intent_modification_styled_area_representation"/> or to help compose a <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_2d_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_2d_design_arm.Stratum_feature_styled_area_representation"/>, only the  <express_ref linkend="Styled_curve:arm:Styled_curve_arm.Curve_style_font"/> shall be referenced by the <express_ref linkend="Styled_curve:arm:Styled_curve_arm.Curve_style.curve_font"/> attribute of the  <express_ref linkend="Styled_curve:arm:Styled_curve_arm.Curve_style"/> Application Object referenced by <b>hatch_line_appearance</b>.
</p><note>
In order to obtain cross-hatch, two instances of <b>Fill_area_style_hatching</b> are required, with complementary angles.
</note>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style_hatching.hatch_line_angle">
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Value_with_unit_extension:arm:Value_with_unit_extension_arm.Angle_data_element"/> for the <b>Fill_area_style_hatching</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style_hatching.pattern_start">
specifies the <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/> for the beginning of the pattern of <b>Fill_area_style_hatching</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style_hatching.point_of_reference_hatch_line">
specifies the <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/> for the point of reference and located on the initial hatch line for the <b>Fill_area_style_hatching</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style_hatching.start_of_next_hatch_line">
specifies the <express_ref linkend="Extended_basic_geometry:arm:Extended_basic_geometry_arm.Vector"/> from the end  <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/> of the present hatch line to the beginning  <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/> of the next hatch line for the <b>Fill_area_style_hatching</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style_hatching.hatch_line_appearance"><p>
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Styled_curve:arm:Styled_curve_arm.Curve_style"/> for the <b>Fill_area_style_hatching</b>.
</p><note>
The curve style may include a discontiguous geometric shape, in which case the hatch cannot be used to represent product data which is contiguous in nature.
</note>
<example>
The curve style may be a dashed line and in that case each of the dashes would correspond to a differenct  <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Stratum_feature"/>.
</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Fill_area_style_tile +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style_tile">

 A <b>Fill_area_style_tile</b> is the definition of the <b>tile</b> for a <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style_tile.tiling_scale">
specifies the role of the integer for a <b>Fill_area_style_tile</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style_tile.tile">
specifies the <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.fill_area_style_tile_shape_select"/> for the <b>Fill_area_style_tile</b>.
The <b>tile</b> specifies either an <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Externally_defined_tile"/>,
 a <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style_tile_curve_with_style"/>, a <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style_tile_solid_region"/>, or 
 a <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style_tile_symbol_with_style"/> for the <b>Fill_area_style_tile</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style_tile.second_direction_repeat_factor">
specifies the <express_ref linkend="Extended_basic_geometry:arm:Extended_basic_geometry_arm.Vector"/> for the <b>Fill_area_style_tile</b>. 
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style_tile.first_direction_repeat_factor">
specifies the <express_ref linkend="Extended_basic_geometry:arm:Extended_basic_geometry_arm.Vector"/> for the <b>Fill_area_style_tile</b>. 
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Fill_area_style_tile_curve_with_style +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style_tile_curve_with_style">

 A <b>Fill_area_style_tile_curve_with_style</b> is the definition of the 
tiling of a <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Fill_area_style_tile_solid_region +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style_tile_solid_region">

 A <b>Fill_area_style_tile_solid_region</b> is the definition of a region 
that shall be filled solidly with tiles.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Fill_area_style_tile_symbol_with_style +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area_style_tile_symbol_with_style">

 A <b>Fill_area_style_tile_symbol_with_style</b> is the definition of a tile 
symbol with a specified style.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Externally_defined_hatch_style +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Externally_defined_hatch_style">

 An <b>Externally_defined_hatch_style</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Hatch_style"/>
 that is defined in an external computer interpretable system.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Externally_defined_tile +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Externally_defined_tile">

 An <b>Externally_defined_tile</b> is a tile that is 
defined in an external computer interpretable system.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Externally_defined_tile_style +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Externally_defined_tile_style">

 An <b>Externally_defined_tile_style</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Tile_style"/> that is defined in an 
external computer interpretable system.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Solid_fill_style +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Solid_fill_style">
A <b>Solid_fill_style</b> is a style of fill pattern that completely fills the <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Fill_area"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Hatch_style +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Hatch_style">
A <b>Hatch_style</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Detailed_geometric_model_element"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Solid_fill_area +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Solid_fill_area">
A <b>Solid_fill_area</b> is a mean to define solid fill area.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Tile_style +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.Tile_style">
A <b>Tile_style</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Detailed_geometric_model_element"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ User_defined_hatch_style +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.User_defined_hatch_style">
A <b>User_defined_hatch_style</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Hatch_style"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.User_defined_hatch_style.hatch_line_appearance">
specifies a role of the <express_ref linkend="Styled_curve:arm:Styled_curve_arm.Curve_appearance"/> for the <b>User_defined_hatch_style</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.User_defined_hatch_style.start_of_next_hatch_line">
specifies a role of the <express_ref linkend="Extended_basic_geometry:arm:Extended_basic_geometry_arm.Vector"/> for the <b>User_defined_hatch_style</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.User_defined_hatch_style.point_of_reference_hatch_line">
specifies a role of the <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/> for the <b>User_defined_hatch_style</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.User_defined_hatch_style.pattern_start">
specifies a role of the <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/> for the <b>User_defined_hatch_style</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.User_defined_hatch_style.hatch_line_angle">
specifies a role of the <express_ref linkend="Value_with_unit_extension:arm:Value_with_unit_extension_arm.Angle_data_element"/> for the <b>User_defined_hatch_style</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.User_defined_hatch_style.wr:WR1">
a type of <express_ref linkend="Styled_curve:arm:Styled_curve_arm.Curve_appearance.font"/> of a <b>hatch_line_appearance</b> shall be <express_ref linkend="Styled_curve:arm:Styled_curve_arm.Solid_curve_font"/>. 
</ext_description> 

<!-- +++++++++++ User_defined_tile_style +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.User_defined_tile_style">
A <b>User_defined_tile_style</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Fill_area_style:arm:Fill_area_style_arm.Tile_style"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.User_defined_tile_style.first_direction_repeat_factor">
specifies a role of the <express_ref linkend="Extended_basic_geometry:arm:Extended_basic_geometry_arm.Vector"/> for the <b>User_defined_tile_style</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.User_defined_tile_style.second_direction_repeat_factor">
specifies a role of the <express_ref linkend="Extended_basic_geometry:arm:Extended_basic_geometry_arm.Vector"/> for the <b>User_defined_tile_style</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Fill_area_style_arm.User_defined_tile_style.tiling_scale">
specifies an integer value of a tiling scale.
</ext_description>

</ext_descriptions>

